<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=john_u_8&Board=bards&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View John (john_u_8) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Most Bards quit early because you don't have all of the more powerful line of songs before level 16 (I.e. Necro) and you have an exp penalty (I don't even notice it).<br>
If you like a bard by the time you are level 15, then you'll LOVE it when you are level 30+. They are very strong soloers that always have a way out and are the drug supplier for a group of not only melee classes (haste songs), but caster classes as well (clarity songs that stack. Hehe), not to mention they lighten the load off of a healer by using their heal song during and after combat.<p>

They can twist up to 5 songs at one time (some songs have longer than a 6 second duration) but only 3 can be played consistantly. They get a song each level, which means you'll basically be happy at any level. I know you've said this before: "One more level, and I get my spells." Well, imagine saying that EVERY level. Hehe.<p>

Bards are by far the most versatile class you can play (even compared to an enchanter.) 8P Basically, they can do anything any other class can do, but to a lesser extent. They can Charm, Mez, Kite,Fear (and reverse kite), Heal, SoW, Clarity, Buff, Solo, and do very well in groups (this is just the highlights). They may not be able to teleport, but when you're level 30 or so, you can travel at UNREAL speeds to your destination.<p>

A final note... When you're a bard of the mid levels or higher, you will always have the opportunity to group. It gives me a sense of gratification to know that others know what I am capable of and are never afraid to group with me (I.e. Rogues).<p>

Post Scriptus: I can't guarantee that you will like a Bard, but what I can tell you is this...<br>
Ask any high level Bard and they will gladly tell you that they do not regret their choice of class.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
