<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I think that the reason some folks don't like bards is:<p>

a. They are simply misunderstood.  The effects of their spells are often subtle at low levels.<br>
b. It's a hard class to play well.  Enchanters are similar.<br>
c. It requires manipulation of the user interface to a great extent.  A lot of folks would rather not think that hard.<br>
d. It's not viewed as a manly class by some.<p>

The class has a lot of color and panache.  Bards do a lot of things very well.  When players get to the point where they've played with bards and understand their spells, they always want one in their group.  I know my Enchanter does, and not just for additional mana regen.<hr>The trick is to die but rarely.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
