<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hmmph, if you can't see the strength that a bard has, you are either, blind, dumb (I'm trying not to be childish, but in this case that's impossible I fear :), or both...take your pick. We can solo quite well in many ways--In some cases way faster and more efficiently that other classes. While I won't say we come anywhere near to necros in our soloing power, you really cant compare us, as our methods of accomplishing this are dramatically different. Our real power, however, is truly in groups...in battle we are capable of adding enough power for 2 people, rather than one, indirectly. And no caster complains that we are walking mana batteries...If you look at a bard and discard them as being weak for their limited damage potential just by themselves, then you really should keep going until you see the ogre warrior :) to see our true power you have to look a bit deeper than all the pretty damage numbers that flash by during battle :) I won't even bother going into our utility songs, because if you are still reading this, you are probably nodding your head in agreement and know all of this anyway, and if this entire message is incomprehensible, it's just because I wrote it way way way too late at night :D<br>
G'night fellow musicians! Greet the dawn with a song and smite ignorance down where it stands!!<p>

(Oh, and about the exp penalty we recieve, you really will never notice it, if you are soloing and doing it properly, you have NO downtime, and if you are grouping and the group understands how you work, you have very little downtime...Verant just cursed us this way to discourage non-believers because they don't want our secrets to be let out, but I say let the whole world know!)<p>

~Quivalen Dawnsinger~<br>
&lt;Moonlite Knights&gt;<br>
